            . On the 13th of December, about twelve o'clock, I was under the <placeName id="t18201206-207-crimeloc1208">Colonade, Pall-mall</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18201206-207-crimeloc1208" type="placeName" value="Colonade, Pall-mall"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18201206-207-crimeloc1208" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18201206-207-off1206 t18201206-207-crimeloc1208"></join>, and felt a catch at my pocket, I turned round, and saw my handkerchief between the prisoners. I secured Clark, Jones got away - he followed us to the watch-house; I afterwards saw him by a picture-shop in Piccadilly, and secured him - I am sure he is the man. I picked my handkerchief up off Clark's feet - I saw him holding it out to Jones, but on seeing me he let it fall.</p>
               <p>JONES'S Defence. I was looking at a shop, and the gentleman took me.</p>
               <p>CLARK - <rs id="t18201206-207-verdict1209" type="verdictDescription">
